<h2 class="related-items-title">Related items</h2>
<div class="related-item related-item1">
<div class="field field-type-link field-field-related-item1"><h3 class="field-label">related_item1</h3><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item"><a href="http://rabble.ca/news/2015/01/should-canada-stockpile-oil-while-prices-are-low" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Should Canada stockpile oil while prices are low?</a></div></div></div><div class="field field-type-text field-field-related-item1-desc"><h3 class="field-label">related_item1_desc</h3><div class="field-items"> <div class="field-item">With oil prices so low, is now the time to stockpile our emergency oil reserves? And if we do, can we phase out to a low carbon future?</div></div></div></div>

<div class="related-item related-item2">
<div class="field field-type-link field-field-related-item2"><h3 class="field-label">related_item2</h3><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item"><a href="http://rabble.ca/columnists/2015/02/deficit-harper-government-refuses-to-recognize">The deficit the Harper government refuses to recognize</a></div></div></div><div class="field field-type-text field-field-related-item2-desc"><h3 class="field-label">related_item2_desc</h3><div class="field-items"> <div class="field-item">Finance Minister Joe Oliver does not want to recognize that spending on public infrastructure is a good way of strengthening a weak Canadian economy.</div></div></div></div>

<div class="related-item related-item3">
<div class="field field-type-link field-field-related-item3"><h3 class="field-label">related_item3</h3><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item"><a href="http://rabble.ca/blogs/bloggers/karl-nerenberg/2015/01/house-returns-and-harper-will-have-to-answer-economic-turmoil" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">The House returns and Harper will have to answer for economic turmoil</a></div></div></div><div class="field field-type-text field-field-related-item3-desc"><h3 class="field-label">related_item3_desc</h3><div class="field-items"> <div class="field-item">Prime Minister Harper now says falling prices in the oil and gas sector are good for the rest of the economy. Still, Finance Minister Oliver has postponed his budget because of market uncertainty.</div></div></div></div>
